{
  "stem": "1062.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "This supposedly is to remind the Jews that they were-- were standing on Mount Sinai because it looked like a-- like a mountain there, you know.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Rosh Hashanah-- even so we were a small village, we used to hire the best [HEBREW] the best [HEBREW] in the area because we appreciated a good chazzan.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And as a matter of fact, to this day, I am the [HEBREW] here in the Shelter Rock Jewish Center, which is a modern Orthodox-- I mean, a modern conservative congregation.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "We have about 700 members in our congregation.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And I'm the [HEBREW].",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And I still daven on the same nusach, on the same-- the way I remember it from my hometown.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And it's surprising to know that many time, young people walk over to me.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And they say, you know something, I really appreciate the way you-- the way you daven because it has a certain Jewish [HEBREW] to it which was squeezed out in America.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "I don't know what happened to it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "But it's-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Yom Kippur.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Night.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "I want you to know that our village didn't have no electricity.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, the first time they brought in electricity to my village was in the '80s, maybe about 15 years ago, for the first time that my village was electrified.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And so in shul, they used to-- every family would come with a huge candle, about 3 feet high.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And there was a table.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And they would mount those candles on the table.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "So when you walked into shul in Yom Kipper night, everything was dark-- [HEBREW] night, I'm talking about.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "But you see about 26 candles in the main.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "It gave it a certain flavor.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "It gave it a certain holiness, a certain awe.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
